# Backend Rules

## Architecture

Use modular monolith.

Do not add:
- microservices
- API Gateway
- RabbitMQ
- Kafka
- event-driven architecture
- complex role permission
- unnecessary abstractions

## Package structure

Use package by feature/module:

- common
- student
- classroom
- tuitionpackage
- enrollment
- studentpackage
- classsession
- attendance
- invoice
- payment
- debt
- dashboard
- statistics
- report
- auth

Use:
- Classroom instead of Class.
- ClassSession for lesson sessions.
- StudentPackage for selected student package/cycle.
- Invoice for tuition fee to collect.
- Payment for actual money received.

## Module structure

Each module should follow:

- Entity
- Enum if needed
- Repository
- Service
- Controller
- dto/
- mapper/

Example:

student/
- Student.java
- StudentStatus.java
- StudentRepository.java
- StudentService.java
- StudentController.java
- dto/
- mapper/

## Controller rules

- Keep controllers thin.
- Controllers receive request DTO.
- Controllers call service.
- Controllers return ApiResponse.
- Do not put business logic in controllers.
- Do not expose JPA entities directly.

## Service rules

- Put business logic in services.
- Use @Transactional for operations involving money or multiple writes.
- Validate business rules in services.
- Throw BusinessException for business rule violations.
- Save ActivityLog for important operations.

## Entity rules

- Do not expose entities to frontend.
- Avoid complex bidirectional relationships unless needed.
- Avoid @Data on JPA entities.
- Use BigDecimal for money.
- Use LocalDate, LocalTime, LocalDateTime for date/time.

## DTO rules

- Use request/response DTOs.
- Use Bean Validation on request DTO.
- Keep response DTO friendly for frontend.
- Do not return unnecessary nested objects.

## Exception rules

Use:
- BusinessException
- NotFoundException
- GlobalExceptionHandler
- Error response format

Do not throw generic RuntimeException for business cases.

## Transaction rules

Use @Transactional for:
- Enrollment creating student package and invoice.
- Payment create.
- Payment cancel.
- Invoice cancel.
- Attendance marking.
- Session cancellation.
- Package change.

## Money rules

- Use BigDecimal.
- Do not use double/float.
- Do not allow manual paidAmount editing.
- Recalculate invoice after payment create/cancel.
- Add tests.
